What is GIT
Git is a distributed version control system (VCS) designed to track changes in source code during software development. It allows multiple developers to work on a project simultaneously, manage changes, and collaborate efficiently

What is GITHUB
GitHub is a web-based platform that provides hosting for software development and version control using Git.

Key features of GitHub include:
-> Repository Hosting: Users can create repositories to store and manage their code. Repositories can be public or private.

-> Version Control: GitHub leverages Gitâ€™s version control system, allowing users to commit changes, create branches, merge code, and handle version histories efficiently.

->Collaboration Tools: GitHub supports collaborative features such as pull requests, code reviews, issues, and discussions, making it easier for teams to work together on projects.
